<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 12:43:16 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>科学家首次捕捉到像波一样运动的反物质“原子”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/scientists-catch-antimatter-atom-acting-like-a-wave-for-the-first-time</link><description>量子物理学曾经揭示粒子可以表现得像波一样震惊科学家，而现在，这种奇怪的行为被进一步推动。研究人员首次观察到正电子素中的波状干扰，正电子素是一种由电子及其反物质伙伴正电子组成的奇异“原子”。这一突破不仅强化了量子力学的怪异现实，而且还为涉及反物质的新实验打开了大门，包括测试重力如何影响它的可能性——这是以前从未直接测量过的东西。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-catch-antimatter-atom-acting-like-a-wave-for-the-first-time.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 12:43:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/scientists-catch-antimatter-atom-acting-like-a-wave-for-the-first-time</guid></item><item><title>人工智能可以帮助人类科学家选择有前途的研究课题</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-could-help-human-scientists-pick-promising-research-topics</link><description>德国卡尔斯鲁厄理工学院 (KIT) 的科学家表示，大型语言模型 (LLM) 可以帮助人类科学家识别以前从未探索过的有趣的研究主题。通过分析材料科学出版物中的摘要并映射不同概念之间的联系，该模型能够生成对未来感兴趣领域的预测，KIT 团队表示，这些预测比传统的基于规则的算法产生的预测更精确。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-could-help-human-scientists-pick-promising-research-topics2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 12:28:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-could-help-human-scientists-pick-promising-research-topics</guid></item><item><title>在侵袭性乳腺癌小鼠模型中，自愿锻炼抵消了热量限制的抗转移作用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-antimetastatic-effects-of-calorie-restriction-are-negated-by-voluntary-exercise-in-an-aggressive-breast-cancer-mouse-model</link><description>生活方式干预对于治疗成功的作用对于几乎所有疾病都至关重要。健康的饮食习惯、定期锻炼和压力管理是改善治疗期间生活质量以及延缓疾病发作和进展的关键支柱。在这项研究中，我们使用 4T1 小鼠模型，重点关注将轻度热量限制 (CR) 和自愿运动结合起来作为化疗的辅助治疗三阴性乳腺癌。在该模型中，在原发肿瘤大小、身体成分或身体机能方面，自愿锻炼并没有比化疗加 CR 带来更多益处，同时削弱了 CR 在久坐小鼠肺部的抗转移作用。这些发现凸显了将结果从一种临床前模型转化为另一种模型并最终转化为人类所面临的挑战。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-antimetastatic-effects-of-calorie-restriction-are-negated-by-voluntary-exercise-in-an-aggressive-breast-cancer-mouse-model2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 12:13:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-antimetastatic-effects-of-calorie-restriction-are-negated-by-voluntary-exercise-in-an-aggressive-breast-cancer-mouse-model</guid></item><item><title>逐个细胞分析揭示了六种神经精神疾病的 345 个风险基因</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/cell-by-cell-analysis-uncovers-345-risk-genes-across-six-neuropsychiatric-disorders</link><description>众所周知，神经精神疾病（影响各种大脑功能和行为的疾病）的出现是由复杂的因素组合驱动的。这些可能包括遗传倾向和暴露于创伤事件或其他外部环境。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cell-by-cell-analysis-uncovers-345-risk-genes-across-six-neuropsychiatric-disorders2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 11:58:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/cell-by-cell-analysis-uncovers-345-risk-genes-across-six-neuropsychiatric-disorders</guid></item><item><title>奥斯卡禁止在表演和写作类别中使用生成式人工智能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-oscars-bans-generative-ai-in-acting-and-writing-categories</link><description>美国电影艺术与科学学院（可能更广为人知的是奥斯卡奖的颁发者）已经明确反对使用生成式人工智能，并更改了其资格规则以排除人工智能生成的表演和剧本。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-oscars-bans-generative-ai-in-acting-and-writing-categories.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 11:43:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-oscars-bans-generative-ai-in-acting-and-writing-categories</guid></item><item><title>路透社行业消息人士称，受伊朗战争影响，PCB价格上涨高达40%</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/pcb-prices-have-risen-by-up-to-40-due-to-war-in-iran-according-to-reuters-industry-sources</link><description>据“行业消息人士和高管”称&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/pcb-prices-have-risen-by-up-to-40-due-to-war-in-iran-according-to-reuters-industry-sources2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 11:28:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/pcb-prices-have-risen-by-up-to-40-due-to-war-in-iran-according-to-reuters-industry-sources</guid></item><item><title>你没疯，《半条命 2》中的下水道谜题确实以前更难</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/youre-not-crazy-that-one-sewer-puzzle-in-half-life-2-really-did-used-to-be-harder</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 11:13:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/youre-not-crazy-that-one-sewer-puzzle-in-half-life-2-really-did-used-to-be-harder</guid></item><item><title>脂肪-脑轴的代谢炎症</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/metabolic-inflammation-at-the-adipose-brain-axis</link><description>代谢炎症中的脂肪脑轴。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/metabolic-inflammation-at-the-adipose-brain-axis.jpg" /&gt; 由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 10:58:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/metabolic-inflammation-at-the-adipose-brain-axis</guid></item><item><title>牛津物理学家在量子物理学领域取得首次“四重挤压”突破</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/oxford-physicists-achieve-first-ever-quadsqueezing-breakthrough-in-quantum-physics</link><description>科学家们创造了一种强大的新方法来控制量子系统，首次演示了四边压缩——一种难以捉摸的四阶量子效应。通过以巧妙的方式组合简单的力，他们使以前隐藏的量子行为变得可见和可用，为量子技术开辟了新的前沿。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/oxford-physicists-achieve-first-ever-quadsqueezing-breakthrough-in-quantum-physics.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 10:43:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/oxford-physicists-achieve-first-ever-quadsqueezing-breakthrough-in-quantum-physics</guid></item><item><title>ESIG-Net：一种解码单突变蛋白质代码的交互语言模型</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/esig-net-an-interaction-language-model-that-decodes-the-protein-code-of-single-mutations-methods</link><description>ESIG-Net 是一种相互作用语言模型，可预测突变对蛋白质相互作用的影响。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/esig-net-an-interaction-language-model-that-decodes-the-protein-code-of-single-mutations-methods.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 May 2026 10:28:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/esig-net-an-interaction-language-model-that-decodes-the-protein-code-of-single-mutations-methods</guid></item></channel></rss>